$ C-Sharp: read settings from an App.exe.config file

gh|.NET-API|/System/Configuration/ConfigurationManager/read-settings/App.cs||

{ Sample config file

  The config file must be named `app-name.exe.config`, for this example `App.exe.config`:

  gh|.NET-API|/System/Configuration/ConfigurationManager/read-settings/App.exe.config.github||

}
{ Creating and running executable

  We use the C-Sharp compiler `csc.exe` to turn the source code `App.cs` into an
  → Windows/development/Portable-Executable/EXE[executable].

  If there is also an `App.exe.config` file, we remove it:
  gh|.NET-API|/System/Configuration/ConfigurationManager/read-settings/compile.ps1||

  Running the exe *with* …
  gh|.NET-API|/System/Configuration/ConfigurationManager/read-settings/run-with.ps1||
 
  … and *without* the config file:
  gh|.NET-API|/System/Configuration/ConfigurationManager/read-settings/run-with.ps1||

}
sa:

  The → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Configuration/ConfigurationManager[`system.Configuration.ConfigurationManager` class].

  → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Configuration/ConfigurationManager/modify-config
